<TITLE> Kenya's Kibaki takes oath for second term </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NAIROBI, Dec 30 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - President Mwai Kibaki took the oath of office on Sunday for a second five-year term within an hour of being declared winner of the 2007 election. "I will be faithful to the Republic of Kenya," Kibaki said, with his hand on a Bible on the lawn of his State House office and residence. As he spoke, riots were erupting in several pro-opposition Nairobi slums.
